 **34.8** |\n| Squad deaths / fight | 1.23 | 1.20 |\n| Kill ratio (enemy deaths : squad deaths) | 10.8 : 1 | **29 : 1** |\n| Total enemy deaths | 292 | 348 |\n\n**A K Baba — high-tempo grinder.** More than double the fight count (22), against near-even enemy numbers (24 vs 31). The squad took losses (5) and steadier attrition, suggesting frequent re-engages and skirmishy pressure rather than waiting for the perfect setup. Damage was led by Riki.6042 on a power Berserker (9.17M) — a melee-spike pick that fits a fast, aggressive cadence.\n\n**D R A F T — patient, decisive blob-buster.** Only 10 fights but went undefeated, and notably picked *larger* enemy groups (39 avg, the biggest of the night) yet still posted a 29:1 kill ratio with just 12 squad deaths. ~35 enemy kills per fight means these were big, committed engagements that ended in collapses, not trades. esko.9832 (Evoker, 7.75M) and SyNNex's Reaper led damage/strips.\n\n**Build swaps between the two tags** are worth noting — several players re-specced for each commander: Riki ran Berserker under Baba but Evoker under DRAFT; Schoko went Necromancer→Reaper; Lilbiand Warrior→Paragon. That hints the two commanders ask for somewhat different squad setups.\n\nNet read: **Baba keeps the squad busy and applies constant pressure across many even fights; DRAFT picks fewer, larger fights and wins them clean.** If you want, I can compare boon/strip coverage or cleanse output between the two runs to see whether the support setup differs as much as the engage style does.","filedAt":"1:28 PM","tools":[{"name":"axibridge_repos_status","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title":"Linked AxiBridge repos","columns":[{"key":"repo","label":"Repo"},{"key":"runs","label":"Runs"},{"key":"firstRun","label":"First run"},{"key":"lastRun","label":"Last run"},{"key":"cachedReports","label":"Cached"},{"key":"stale","label":"Live?"},{"key":"error","label":"Error"}],"rows":[{"repo":"ChromaticOrb/axibridge","runs":25,"firstRun":"2026-03-23T20: