 doesn't tell you:\n\n- **Both enemy groups were power-pressure comps.** Roughly 93–96% of the damage our squad ate was direct/power, with condition damage a minor sliver. That points to a power-spike-based opponent (think power melee trains and burst), not a condi-bomb composition. Under DRAFT — the bigger blob — the damage was even more purely power (96%).\n- **The condition-applications field came back empty** (0 applications in `conditions_in` for both runs), so I can't break the incoming condi down by type — the only condi signal is the raw damage number above.\n- **I cannot name the opposing professions, server, or build mix.** AxiBridge constructs reports from our own squad's log, so there is no enemy class distribution, enemy boon/strip output, or enemy roster — that data simply isn't published.\n\nIf you want a real read on who you were fighting, the practical route is the enemy tag/server name from the matchup or a screenshot — AxiBridge won't reconstruct it. Want me to instead dig into how *our* squad's defenses held up against that power pressure (barrier absorbed, mitigation, where deaths clustered)?","filedAt":"1:41 PM","tools":[{"name":"axibridge_find","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title":"Sections for \"enemy composition professions faced opponent classes\"","columns":[{"key":"section","label":"Section"},{"key":"title","label":"What"},{"key":"granularities","label":"Granularity"}],"rows":[{"section":"class_distribution","title":"Class distribution","granularities":"squad"}]}}},{"name":"axibridge_find","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title":"Sections for \"damage taken from enemy sources, incoming conditions by enemy profession\"","columns":[{"key":"section","label":"Section"},{"key":"title","label":"What"},{"key":"granularities","label":"Granularity"}],"rows":[{"section":"conditions_in","title":"Incoming conditions","granularities":"player, squad"},{"section":"damage_taken","title":"Damage taken","granularities":"player, squad"},{"section":"c